[FEN "1r1qrb1k/5p2/4pP2/2ppPpQ1/np1p4/p2P4/R5B1/2B1R1K1 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.08.03"]
[UTCTime "02:16:38"]

1... b3 { Black attempts to ignore all the dangers on the kingside and push through on the queenside with those two advanced passed pawns. How should White respond to this threat? Hmmm.... The answer is to ignore it! So what if Black promotes to a queen or even 2 queens? White has checkmate, game over! } 2. Kf2! { Sacrificing the rook on a2. It doesn't matter. The Rook on e1 is the key one to deliver checkmate } 2... bxa2 3. Rh1+ { Checkmate next move. } *


